WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.520
Welcome to the test set. Here we talk with some of the brightest thinkers and tinkerers

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:11.560
in statistical analysis, scientific computing, and machine learning, digging into what makes

00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:18.440
them tick, plus the insights, experiments, and OMG moments that shape the field. On this

00:00:18.440 --> 00:00:24.200
episode, we sit down with Hadley Wickham, Hall of Fame statistician, open source programmer,

00:00:24.280 --> 00:00:29.240
and chief scientist at Posit. I'm Michael Chow. Thanks for joining us.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:38.119
You're the chief scientist at Posit, formerly RStudio, and you created this really great

00:00:38.119 --> 00:00:48.439
ecosystem of R packages for making data analysis delightful in R. And you work on the tidyverse,

00:00:48.439 --> 00:00:52.680
which is a collection of tools in R. And as you're wearing the tidyverse socks.

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:56.200
Yeah, I've got a little, I'm repping the tidyverse a little bit.

